article.headline: North Dakota 86, Texas-Pan American 60
article.story: GRAND FORKS, N.D. -- Jamal Webb scored 19 points to lead five North Dakota players in double figures in an 86-60 victory over Texas-Pan American on Monday night. Aaron Anderson added 15 points for the Sioux (14-14, 5-4 Great West), which won its third in a row and ninth straight at home. Patrick Mitchell, Lenny Antwi and Josh Schuler scored 11 points apiece, and Webb had eight assists and eight rebounds. Josh Cleveland's 15-point, 11-rebound effort, his first career double-double, paced the Broncs (11-19, 5-4). Jared Maree added 10 points. North Dakota shot 54 percent (31 of 57), including 14 of 28 from 3-point range. The Sioux bolted to a 10-0 advantage, were up 44-20 at intermission and coasted from there. Texas-Pan American and North Dakota are now tied for second place behind league champion Utah Valley. The teams split the season series, the Broncs having won 70-58 on Jan. 28.
